<subSubSection id="C374657AC315FF9CFF419AAE5D914389" pageId="14" pageNumber="391" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD136F1C315FF9CFF419AAE5DB340DD" blockId="14.[151,1437,402,647]" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C315FF9CFF419AAE5F2040A0" bold="true" box="[151,307,402,428]" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">Distribution:</emphasis>
Western Amazonia of 
<collectingCountry id="F3797661C315FF9CFDE49AAF5C6A40A1" box="[562,633,403,429]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, north 
<collectingCountry id="F3797661C315FF9CFD109AAF5CEA40A1" box="[710,761,403,429]" name="Peru" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">Peru</collectingCountry>
and southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3797661C315FF9CFC419AAF5A1640A1" box="[919,1029,403,429]" name="Colombia" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B00C315FF9CFBC59AAF5B6040A1" author="Ribeiro-Junior, M. A. &amp; Amaral, S." box="[1043,1395,403,429]" pageId="14" pageNumber="391" pagination="151 - 196" refId="ref18425" refString="Ribeiro-Junior, M. A. &amp; Amaral, S. (2017) Catalogue of distribution of lizards (Reptilia: Squamata) from the Brazilian Amazonia. IV. Alopoglossidae, Gymnophthalmidae. Zootaxa, 4269 (2), 151 - 196. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4269.2.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Ribeiro-Júnior &amp; Amaral 2017</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="F3797661C315FF9CFF419A8B5F1640DD" box="[151,261,439,465]" name="Colombia" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">Colombia</collectingCountry>
it is known only from the 
<collectingRegion id="49AAF813C315FF9CFDF89A8B5D3A40DD" box="[558,809,439,465]" country="Colombia" name="Amazonas" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">Amazonas department</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="13552A74C315FF9CFCEE9A8B5D8040DD" box="[824,915,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[217,1370,181,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[217,1370,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Distribution maps for the cis-Andean microteiid lizards in Colombia (Alopoglossidae + Gymnophthalmidae). Circles are examined specimens, while squares are records from literature (see Supplementary Files for specific references). Red arrows indicate new records for Colombia. Black arrows show a zoom in to regions where several records overlap. The light green shadow indicates the Orinoco River basin, and the dark green the Amazon River basin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5681929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5681929/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136F1C315FF9CFF119AE65D914389" blockId="14.[151,1437,402,647]" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C315FF9CFF119AE65F9040F8" bold="true" box="[199,387,474,500]" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">Similar species:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D72C315FF9CFE5D9AE75C8640F9" baseAuthorityName="Avila-Pires" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[395,661,475,501]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="391" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="snethlageae">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C315FF9CFE5D9AE75C8640F9" box="[395,661,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">Loxopholis snethlageae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from its congenerics by the presence of a large fourth pair of chin-shields (reduced in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D72C315FF9CFE7C9AC35C214315" baseAuthorityName="Ayala &amp; Harris" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[426,562,511,537]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="391" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hexalepis">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C315FF9CFE7C9AC35C214315" box="[426,562,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">L. hexalepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D72C315FF9CFDB19AC35D0F4314" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[615,796,511,536]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="391" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="percarinatum">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C315FF9CFDB19AC35D0F4314" box="[615,796,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">L. percarinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); sharply keeled ventral scales (smooth or weakly keeled in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D72C315FF9CFF60991F5F5E4330" baseAuthorityName="Esqueda" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[182,333,547,572]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="391" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caparensis">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C315FF9CFF60991F5F5E4330" box="[182,333,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">L. caparensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, smooth in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D72C315FF9CFE00991F5C4C4331" baseAuthorityName="Ayala &amp; Harris" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[470,607,547,573]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="391" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hexalepis">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C315FF9CFE00991F5C4C4331" box="[470,607,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">L. hexalepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); hexagonal to quadrangular or lanceolate dorsal scales, and third supraocular larger than the second (rhomboid dorsal scales and second supraocular subequal or largest than third in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D72C315FF9CFA50997B5F114389" baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1886" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="391" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parietalis">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C315FF9CFA50997B5F114389" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="391">L. parietalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). For a more detailed description see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B00C315FF9CFD7C99505D6C4389" author="Avila-Pires, T." box="[682,895,618,647]" pageId="14" pageNumber="391" pagination="1 - 706" refId="ref15408" refString="Avila-Pires, T. (1995) Lizards of Brazilian Amazonia (Reptilia: Squamata). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 299, 1 - 706." type="journal article" year="1995">Ávila-Pires (1995)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
